<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id748bc104-3a70-11f1-9d9e-dfac6d46cab7" identifier="/us/usc/t36/s90106"><num value="90106">§ 90106.</num><heading> Principal office</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">The principal office of the foundation shall be in the District of Columbia unless the board of directors determines otherwise. However, the foundation may conduct business throughout the States, territories, and possessions of the United States.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="id748bc105-3a70-11f1-9d9e-dfac6d46cab7">(Added <ref href="/us/pl/107/252/tVI/s601/a">Pub. L. 107–252, title VI, § 601(a)</ref>, <date date="2002-10-29">Oct. 29, 2002</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/116/1720">116 Stat. 1720</ref>, § 152606; renumbered § 90106, <ref href="/us/pl/113/237/s3/c/6/B">Pub. L. 113–237, § 3(c)(6)(B)</ref>, <date date="2014-12-18">Dec. 18, 2014</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/128/2840">128 Stat. 2840</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
